text.tspan: Every vertex is connected to 6 other vertices via edges, so in an
unit cell there must be one vertex and thre edge in three direction
combining these unit cell will give a lattice structure of
Each Horizontal edge of a cell connects the vertex in the currect cell and the next cell on the right
Each Vertical edge of a cell connects the vertex in the currect cell and the next cell on the bottom
Each Diagonal edge of a cell connects the vertex in the currect cell and the next cell on the right bottom
